                            <comment id="17681815" author="edimitrova" created="Sun, 29 Jan 2023 23:53:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting the problem. Indeed the website doesn&apos;t load anything with any of the versions 3.11+ when I go to Tools -&amp;gt; nodetool&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CC Josh &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stefan.miklosovic&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stefan.miklosovic&quot;&gt;stefan.miklosovic&lt;/a&gt;&#160;,&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=erickramirezau&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;erickramirezau&quot;&gt;erickramirezau&lt;/a&gt;&#160;and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=polandll&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;polandll&quot;&gt;polandll&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17681925" author="smiklosovic" created="Mon, 30 Jan 2023 07:37:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am not sure why this is happening, yet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in index.adoc there is&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
* xref:tools/cqlsh.adoc[CQL shell]
* xref:tools/nodetool/nodetool.adoc[nodetool]
* xref:tools/sstable/index.adoc[SSTable tools] 
* xref:tools/cassandra_stress.adoc[cassandra-stress tool]
* xref:tools/hash_password.adoc[hash password tool]
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which seems to be just right.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the link &quot;nodetool&quot; points to &quot;https://cassandra.apache.org/doc/latest/cassandra/tools/index.html#tools/nodetool/nodetool.adoc&quot; which does not do anything.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;EDIT:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;also, there does not seem to be page about hash password tool added.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
* xref:tools/hash_password.adoc[hash password tool]
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;EDIT:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the nodetool generation is broken by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18197&quot; title=&quot;Builds being often aborted because of python3 ./scripts/gen-nodetool-docs.py being slow&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-18197&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-18197&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have checked out just commit before that was merged and it rendered it properly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=brandon.williams&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;brandon.williams&quot;&gt;brandon.williams&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17682075" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 30 Jan 2023 13:02:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure how that broke it and it seems to work on my machine, but let&apos;s just revert: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/driftx/cassandra/tree/CASSANDRA-18207-3.11&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;3.11&lt;/a&gt;.  I don&apos;t think we need CI for this but I can run the matrix if someone would like.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17682076" author="smiklosovic" created="Mon, 30 Jan 2023 13:06:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;have you tried to generate website before and after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18197&quot; title=&quot;Builds being often aborted because of python3 ./scripts/gen-nodetool-docs.py being slow&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-18197&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-18197&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;? It did not work after the latter for me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17682079" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 30 Jan 2023 13:16:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I ran it before, copied the entire doc dir and made it a git repo, ran it after and copied that dir over it, then inspected the output of &apos;git diff&apos;, which was only my patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17682087" author="smiklosovic" created="Mon, 30 Jan 2023 13:35:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;./run.sh website build -g -u cassandra:/home/smiklosovic/dev/cassandra/cassandra-instaclustr/cassandra -b cassandra:generation&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;generation&quot; branch is commit 93cc75ccdfd6747aa2e5b2344496a99c62e39d8a&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is what I see in the output:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
gen-asciidoc:
     [exec] python3 ./scripts/gen-nodetool-docs.py
     [exec] Makefile:23: recipe &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; target &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;gen-asciidoc&apos;&lt;/span&gt; failed
     [exec]   File &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;./scripts/gen-nodetool-docs.py&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, line 50
     [exec]     &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (batch := tuple(islice(it, n))):
     [exec]                  ^
     [exec] SyntaxError: invalid syntax
     [exec] make: *** [gen-asciidoc] Error 1
     [exec] Result: 2
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I removed apache/cassandra-website:latest image to be sure that the website-building script will download all again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17682088" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 30 Jan 2023 13:38:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You need python 3.8 for the walrus operator.  It is simple to fix that if we need support for lesser versions, though that&apos;s a concern in itself.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17682091" author="smiklosovic" created="Mon, 30 Jan 2023 13:46:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Doesnt website image have Python 3.6 bundled? I see the exact same behavior when building it locally. &lt;br/&gt;
So we need to either downgrade the patch or upgrade the version of Python in the image, right? I would prefer the latter.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17682093" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 30 Jan 2023 13:48:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that removes the operator: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/driftx/cassandra/commit/d7512785ee35366a4d13337efa6a4322204163f1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/driftx/cassandra/commit/d7512785ee35366a4d13337efa6a4322204163f1&lt;/a&gt; and should work with python 3.6. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;upgrade the version of Python in the image, right? I would prefer the latter.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be good to upgrade, certainly, though that is perhaps out of scope here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17682102" author="smiklosovic" created="Mon, 30 Jan 2023 14:03:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, this works! It renders it fine now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
